** Who we are **

FloodMapp is a rapidly growing technology company with the important mission
to build a safer future. Flooding is the costliest natural disaster, causing
billions in damage and taking thousands of lives across the globe every year.
FloodMapp delivers real-time flood intelligence to emergency managers,
supporting them to prepare, respond and recover from flood events. We work
with asset owners to prevent damaged streamline recovery efforts to keep
lights on and roads open. We work with government agencies to improve safety
and save lives through targeted evacuations, road closures and swift water
rescue. In the face of a changing climate, we help communities adapt, to
increase resilience, and recover from disasters.

At FloodMapp, people are our main focus, because hard problems require an
exceptional team. As a diverse team, we value empathy, integrity,
accountability and communication. Everyone learns from each other. Everyone is
passionate about solving a growing global problem and making a global impact.
We all work to build a safer future. We believe that the unique ideas brought
from all of our amazing team is one of the keys to our success. To create an
inclusive and diverse culture, we welcome, encourage and celebrate applicants
of any race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual
orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status.

** Your Roles & Responsibilities **

You’ll be working within our Flood Operations team to create and deploy real-
time flood models across Australia and the United States to support flood
events. You’ll monitor flood operations and advise emergency managers across
government and critical infrastructure. You’ll help provide training and
education to our customers about how to interpret flood intelligence results
so that they can make better decisions, in real time. You’ll work with
industry-standard technologies to build benchmarking models, but you’ll also
be exposed to new cutting edge technologies. You’ll learn how to use python to
accomplish complex tasks easily. You’ll learn SQL to allow you to access
surface water records spanning hundreds of years, a dozen agencies, and two
continents.

This will not be consulting work. There are no timesheets, and you’ll be
continually learning and solving big challenges.

** You will spend your day **

  * Developing hydraulic models 
  * Developing hydrology models 
  * Calibrating and validating hydrology and hydraulic models 
  * Generating validation and calibration reports 
  * Monitoring real-time model performance during flood events 

** Your Skills & Background **

_ ** We would love for you to have ** _

  * Currently studying or have recently graduated with a bachelor’s degree in civil or environmental engineering, or equivalent experience 
  * 0-1 years’ experience within the surface water, water resources, or flooding field or relevant practical placement or vacation experience 
  * An understanding and comprehension of hydrological and hydraulic investigations for urban and rural catchments 
  * Interest or experience in flood modelling 
  * Interest or skills in hydraulic and hydrological modelling software packages. 
  * Well-developed oral and written communication skills. 
  * Willing to learn from other colleagues. 

_ ** It’s not required, but would be great if you have ** _

  * Experience with QGIS and/or ArcGIS Pro / Online 
  * Experience with 2D modelling (e.g. HEC-RAS or TUFLOW) 
  * Experience with Python 

** Who we look for **

We believe that the unique ideas from all of our amazing team members are key
to our success. We believe that we need great talent to solve the world’s
toughest challenges.

FloodMapp is a highly dynamic startup environment, so there will be a great
deal of agility required. You should be comfortable with rapid, continuous
problem-solving. Working on large scale problems with novel approaches to
solve huge global challenges requires talent, teamwork and determination.
We’re looking for someone passionate about solving very real and very serious
problems at scale. We’re looking for someone with a mature, professional
attitude and work style. We want people with:

  * Ambition, drive and opinions 
  * Autonomy, and self-direction 
  * An ownership attitude 
  * Curiosity and a growth mindset 
  * Great communication skills 
  * Humility and respect with the ability to excel in a team environment 
  * The passion to create a safer future 
  * We like people like you. 

